proposed_resolution:
User decision on resolution path: (a) pi-coding-agent upstream extension to expose currentModel/currentProvider on ExtensionContext (canonical-source-restoration); (b) jit-agents reads auth.json + env directly without ExtensionContext dependency (canonical-source-relocation); (c) DEC-0001 re-anchor to acknowledge that model resolution happens BEFORE jit-agents' executeAgent receives the dispatch (caller's responsibility, not executeAgent's) — the 'bare model id' problem moves to the caller surface, addressed by caller-side fix (e.g. monitors classifyViaAgent reads session-canonical source itself + constructs Model<Api>). Implementation surfaces in TASK-085 (DEC-0001 impl) post-FGAP-115 resolution.

RESOLUTION (2026-05-30, option d emerged from verification arc): The empirical premise of this FGAP was wrong. Plan-mode 2026-05-26 grep for 'currentModel' / 'currentProvider' returned zero hits correctly — but the field is named 'model' (not 'currentModel') and IS exposed on ExtensionContext at node_modules/@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent/dist/core/extensions/types.d.ts:217-219:

  modelRegistry: ModelRegistry;
  /** Current model (may be undefined) */
  model: Model<any> | undefined;

Both surfaces exist in installed 0.75.4 + remain unchanged through latest 0.78.0 (verified via changelog survey 0.76/0.77/0.78). The canonical source DEC-0001 assumed IS where canon thought — just under a different name than the original investigation searched for.

OPTION (d) — DEC-0001 as-written is implementable via ctx.model + ctx.modelRegistry. Cost near-zero: jit-agents consumes ctx.model where DEC-0001 implementations need current-session model + ctx.modelRegistry.find(provider, modelId) where bare-model-id resolution needs the registry-lookup mechanism. No upstream PR (option a unnecessary); no auth.json side-channel (option b unnecessary); no DEC-0001 narrative re-anchor (option c not needed). The original gap dissolves: the canonical source exists; the implementation path is "use the field that is there."

Verification arc: subagent dispatched 2026-05-30 against pi latest version + changelog impact; report at analysis/2026-05-30-fgap-115-pi-latest-impact.md; subagent finding independently re-verified by orchestrator at the cited file:line; finding is accurate. VER-067 attests.

UNBLOCKS: DEC-0001 implementation work (TASK-085 in .project; TASK-002 in .context-jit-spec-v2 agentic-mode dispatch loop). Both were blocked on this FGAP's resolution; option (d) collapses the precondition to a small consumption-site code change ("use ctx.model + ctx.modelRegistry where appropriate").
